op}}\n| 331\n| 4451.255&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for GT Manufacturers]]\n|-\n! [[1963 24 Hours of Le Mans|1963]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Ludovico Scarfiotti]]<br>{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Lorenzo Bandini]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Scuderia Ferrari|SpA Ferrari SEFAC]]\n| [[Ferrari P|Ferrari 250 P]]\n| {{Dunlop}}\n| 339\n| 4561.71&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for GT Manufacturers]]\n|-\n! [[1964 24 Hours of Le Mans|1964]]\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Jean Guichet]]<br>{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Nino Vaccarella]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Scuderia Ferrari|SpA Ferrari SEFAC]]\n| [[Ferrari P|Ferrari 275 P]]\n| {{Dunlop}}\n| 349\n| 4695.31&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for GT Manufacturers]]\n|-\n! [[1965 24 Hours of Le Mans|1965]]\n| {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Jochen Rindt]]<br>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Masten Gregory]]<br>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Ed Hugus]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[North American Racing Team]]\n| [[Ferrari P|Ferrari 250 LM]]\n| {{Goodyear}}\n| 348\n| 4677.11&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for GT Manufacturers]]\n|-\n! [[1966 24 Hours of Le Mans|1966]]\n| {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Bruce McLaren]]<br>{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Ken Miles]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carroll Shelby International|Shelby-American Inc.]]\n| [[Ford GT40|Ford GT40 Mk. II]]\n| {{Goodyear}}\n| 360\n| 4843.09&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for Sports-Prototypes]]<br>[[International Championship for Sports Cars]]\n|-\n! [[1967 24 Hours of Le Mans|1967]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Dan Gurney]]<br>{{flagicon|USA}} [[A. J. Foyt]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carroll Shelby International|Shelby-American Inc.]]\n| [[Ford GT40|Ford GT40 Mk. IV]]\n| {{Goodyear}}\n| 388\n| 5232.9&nbsp;km\n| [[International Championship for Sports-Prototypes]]<br>[[International Championship for Sports Cars]]\n|-\n! [[1968 24 Hours of Le Mans|1968]]\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Pedro Rodr\u00edguez (racing driver)|Pedro Rodr\u00edguez]]<br>{{flagicon|BEL}} [[Lucien Bianchi]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[John Wyer|J.W. Automotive Engineering]]\n| [[Ford G