==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Driver\n! Consecutive<br/>Wins\n! Years\n|-\n! 1\n| {{flagicon|DNK}} [[Tom Kristensen (racing driver)|Tom Kristensen]]\n|align=center| 6\n| {{24hLM|2000}}\u2013{{24hLM|2005}}\n|-\n!rowspan=7| 2\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Woolf Barnato]]\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"7\"| 3\n| {{24hLM|1928}}\u2013{{24hLM|1930}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Olivier Gendebien]]\n| {{24hLM|1960}}\u2013{{24hLM|1962}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Henri Pescarolo]]\n| {{24hLM|1972}}\u2013{{24hLM|1974}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Jacky Ickx]]\n| {{24hLM|1975}}\u2013{{24hLM|1977}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Emanuele Pirro]]\n| {{24hLM|2000}}\u2013{{24hLM|2002}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Frank Biela]]\n| {{24hLM|2000}}\u2013{{24hLM|2002}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|DEU}} [[Marco Werner]]\n| {{24hLM|2005}}\u2013{{24hLM|2007}}\n|}\n\n====Winning drivers per nation====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Nation\n! Winning<br/>Drivers\n|-\n! 1\n| {{GBR}}\n|align=center| 32\n|-\n! 2\n| {{FRA}}\n|align=center| 29\n|-\n! 3\n| {{DEU}}\n|align=center| 19\n|-\n! 4\n| {{USA}}\n|align=center| 12<ref name=\"Chinetti\">Luigi Chinetti won Le Mans initially as an Italian, but later won as an American.  His wins are included for both countries.</ref>\n|-\n! 5\n| {{ITA}}\n|align=center| 11<ref name=\"Chinetti\" />\n|-\n! 6\n| {{BEL}}\n|align=center| 5\n|-\n! rowspan=2| 7\n| {{AUS}}\n|align=center rowspan=2| 4\n|-\n| {{NZL}}\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 9\n| {{AUT}}\n|align=center rowspan=3| 3\n|-\n| {{JPN}}\n|-\n| {{CHE}}\n|-\n!rowspan=4| 12\n| {{DNK}}\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"4\"| 2\n|-\n| {{NLD}}\n|-\n| {{ESP}}\n|-\n| {{SWE}}\n|-\n!rowspan=4| 16\n| {{ARG}}\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"4\"| 1\n|-\n| {{CAN}}\n|-\n| {{FIN}}\n|-\n| {{MEX}}\n|}\n\n====Total wins per nation====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Nation\n! Wins\n|-\n! 1\n| {{FRA}}\n|align=center| 44\n|-\n! 2\n| {{GBR}}\n|align=center| 42\n|-\n! 3\n| {